" in. Now when you add HTML files to calibre they will be correctly "
"processed. HTML files from different sources often have different encodings,"
" so you may have to change this setting repeatedly. A common encoding for "
"many files from the web is ``cp1252`` and I would suggest you try that "
"first. Note that when converting HTML files, leave the input encoding "
"setting mentioned above blank. This is because the :guilabel:`HTML to ZIP` "
"plugin automatically converts the HTML files to a standard encoding (UTF-8)."
msgstr ""

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:54
msgid "What's the deal with Table of Contents in MOBI files?"
msgstr "Kas ir noticis ar Satura rādītāju MOBI failos?"

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:56
msgid ""
"The first thing to realize is that most e-books have two tables of contents."
" One is the traditional Table of Contents, like the ToC you find in paper "
"books. This Table of Contents is part of the main document flow and can be "
"styled however you like. This ToC is called the *content ToC*."
msgstr "Vispirms ir jāsaprot, ka lielākajai daļai e-grāmatu ir divas satura tabulas. Vienai no tām ir tradicionālais Satura rādītājs, piemēram, to, ko jūs atrodat papīra grāmatās. Šis Saturs rādītājs ir daļa no galvenās dokumentu plūsmas, un to var veidot, kā vēlaties. Šo Satura rādītāju sauc *content ToC*."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:58
msgid ""
"Then there is the *metadata ToC*. A metadata ToC is a ToC that is not part "
"of the book text and is typically accessed by some special button on a "
"reader. For example, in the calibre E-book viewer, you use the Show Table of"
" Contents button to see this ToC. This ToC cannot be styled by the book "
"creator. How it is represented is up to the viewer program."
msgstr ""

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:60
msgid ""
"In the MOBI format, the situation is a little confused. This is because the "
"MOBI format, alone amongst mainstream e-book formats, *does not* have decent"
" support for a metadata ToC. A MOBI book simulates the presence of a "
"metadata ToC by putting an *extra* content ToC at the end of the book. When "
"you click Goto Table of Contents on your Kindle, it is to this extra content"
" ToC that the Kindle takes you."
msgstr "MOBI formātā situācija ir nedaudz mulsinoša. Tas ir tādēļ, ka MOBI formātā, vieni no galvenajiem e-grāmatu formātiem, *nav* ir pienācīgs atbalsts metadatu ToC. MOBI grāmata simulē metadatu uzvedības klātbūtni, grāmatas beigās ievietojot *papildu* saturu ToC. Noklikšķinot uz jūsu Kindle satura rādītāju, šīs papildu ToC, ir tas kas Kindle palaiž."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:62
msgid ""
"Now it might well seem to you that the MOBI book has two identical ToCs. "
"Remember that one is semantically a content ToC and the other is a metadata "
"ToC, even though both might have exactly the same entries and look the same."
" One can be accessed directly from the Kindle's menus, the other cannot."
msgstr "Tagad jums varētu likties, ka MOBI grāmatā ir divas identiskas ToC. Atcerieties, ka semantiskais saturs ir ToC saturs, bet otrs ir metadatu kopija, kaut gan abiem var būt tieši tādi paši ieraksti un tie ir vienādi. Vienam var piekļūt tieši no Kindle izvēlnes, otram nevar."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:64
msgid ""
"When converting to MOBI, calibre detects the *metadata ToC* in the input "
"document and generates an end-of-file ToC in the output MOBI file. You can "
"turn this off by an option in the MOBI Output settings. You can also tell "
"calibre whether to put it at the start or the end of the book via an option "
"in the MOBI Output settings. Remember this ToC is semantically a *metadata "
"ToC*, in any format other than MOBI it *cannot not be part of the text*. The"
" fact that it is part of the text in MOBI is an accident caused by the "
"limitations of MOBI. If you want a ToC at a particular location in your "
"document text, create one by hand. So we strongly recommend that you leave "
"the default as it is, i.e. with the metadata ToC at the end of the book. "
"Also note that if you disable the generation of the end-of-file ToC the "
"resulting MOBI file may not function correctly on a Kindle, since the "
"Kindle's use the metadata ToC for many things, including the Page Flip "
"feature."
msgstr ""

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:66
msgid ""
"If you have a hand edited ToC in the input document, you can use the ToC "
"detection options in calibre to automatically generate the metadata ToC from"
" it. See the conversion section of the User Manual for more details on how "
"to use these options."
msgstr "Ja ievades dokumentā esat ievadījis manuāli pārveidotu ToC, jūs varat izmantot ToC noteikšanas opcijas calibre, lai automātiski ģenerētu no tā metadatus. Plašāku informāciju par to, kā izmantot šīs opcijas, skatiet lietotāja rokasgrāmatas pārveidošanas sadaļā."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:68
msgid ""
"Finally, I encourage you to ditch the content ToC and only have a metadata "
"ToC in your e-books. Metadata ToCs will give the people reading your e-books"
" a much superior navigation experience (except on the Kindle, where they are"
" essentially the same as a content ToC)."
msgstr "Visbeidzot, es aicinu jūs atteikties no satura ToC un lai būtu tikai metadatu ToC jūsu e-grāmatās. Metadatu krājumi nodrošina cilvēkiem, kuri lasīs jūsu e-grāmatas, daudz izcilāku navigācijas pieredzi (izņemot Kindle, jo tie būtībā ir tādi paši kā saturam ToC)."

#: ../../__w/calibre/calibre/manual/faq.rst:71
msgid ""
"The newer AZW3 format has proper support for a metadata ToC. However, the "
"Kindle firmware tends to malfunction if you disable the generation of the "
"end-of-file inline ToC. So it is recommended that you leave the generated "
"ToC alone. If you create an AZW3 file with a metadata ToC and no end-of-file"
" generated ToC, some features on the Kindle will not work, such as the Page "
"Flip feature."
msgstr "Jaunākajam AZW3 formātam ir piemērots metadatu ToC atbalsts. Tomēr Kindle programmaparatūrai ir tendence uz nepareizu darbību, ja atspējojat faila beigu iekšējās iedarbības ģenerēšanu. Tāpēc ieteicams atstāt ģenerēto ToC vienatnē. Ja izveidojat AZW3 failu ar metadatu ToC un bez faila beigu ģenerēta ToC, dažas Kindle funkcijas nedarbosies, piemēram, Page Flip funkcija."

